                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I have the Orb and I have decided I am not a huge fan of using it against the level 59-60 mobs I am fighting because you are forced to either mez the mob and wait to proc it, breaking mez often, or slow the mob waiting to proc it and a slowed pet is no good.  And our undead slow is not cured by Touch of Death although I suppose you could annul magic and break mez which is also rather...dangerous...<br /><br />I like to give the pet -mr gear and it works quite well for me.  Two Adamantite Bands + a Rusty Spiked Shoulderpads = -30 in MR gear.  There are other items out there but I do not have them yet and -30 is plenty for me for now.<br /><br />There will be those who argue that it is a miniscule amount but I am a fan of using every tool in my arsenal and have seen that with 200+ Charisma, I can get WoT to last a fair duration with -30 MR on, say, Highborns in Veksar whereas I have noticed it be substantially less dependable with my regular Charisma of 113...it's worth the 300 hp's I give up to have charm last longer (best cha gear is generally tradeskill trophies that give +50...shamen can also cast a buff on you to increase it dramatically and costs NADA).<br /><br />Most high level mobs regen at an incredible pace.  If you FD to break charm the pet will reset and regen hp's at an incredible pace.<br /><br />Do not give pet toys to or haste your pet until you are a skilled charmer.  They hit hard and fast enough that you will have a devil of a time surviving against same if it breaks and you are not ready for it.  And Veksar mobs are especially dangerous with same because they all summon.  ME is a fantastic place to practice charming...<br /><br />Always root and snare your opponent (and, if possible, snare your pet as well before charming).</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
