                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> No offense taken at all.  You absolutely right about the fact that it is lame that a Necro has to jump through hoops to make WoT useful.  If I did not feel like the hassle was not worth the reward, I would have made a "bitch" thread instead of attempting something constructive though.<br /><br />In my opinion, if used correctly, the spell is well worth the hassle (especially if you are in a situation with outside assistance...a Shaman to Malo, a Ranger to snare, etc.)  <br /><br />When I am plowing through a BB adventure with a pet who is rapidly hitting for 300+ and procing like mad, I guarantee that my group is not pissed about how rotten the spell is.  In fact, they are usually all about offering to tash, snare, etc.  And when you are lucky enough to be grouped with another Necro or an Enchanter, look out!  Mobs are dropping like flies!<br /><br />And that is just in a single area.  The spell is much fun to use in places like Tactics too.  Even without using the faction exploit in that zone, charming can net you some decent experience!<br /><br />Charming is definitely not for everyone; but maybe by collecting some good information about it, those who want to give it a go will live a little longer. :)<br /><br />-Emi</span id="msg"></font></td>
